    "Glaucoma Drainage Devices (GDD): For patientswho may not be ideal candidates for trabeculec-tomy or those who have previously failed trab-eculectomy, GDDs can offer another pathway forfluid drainage, thereby reducing IOP3.",
    "Minimally Invasive Glaucoma Surgery (MIGS):MIGS procedures, which include devices like thegel stent, are designed to offer a safer profile withfewer complications and a quicker recovery whileeffectively managing IOP.",
    "They may be particularlyappealing in cases where the patient's risk profilenecessitates a less invasive approach,Given the information on current advancements andoptions in glaucoma treatment, if I had to chooseone surgical treatment for advanced primary open-angle glaucoma where medical management hasbeen insufficient, I would consider Trabeculectomy.This procedure has a long history of effectivenessin reducing intraocular pressure (IOP) by creating anew drainage pathway for the aqueous humor.",
